(laughing)

00:39:20.260 --> 00:39:23.576
But I've now come to believe that

00:39:23.576 --> 00:39:26.566
the final frontier is going to be time.

00:39:26.566 --> 00:39:29.606
Understanding how the temporal processing

00:39:29.606 --> 00:39:32.450
occurring in different
circuits and delays that occur

00:39:32.450 --> 00:39:36.660
between communication, between
different parts of the brain

00:39:36.660 --> 00:39:39.537
may be critically important
and we've neglected it.

00:39:39.537 --> 00:39:42.447
So I've worked on networks
for my entire career.

00:39:42.447 --> 00:39:44.153
And I've always thought of networks

00:39:44.153 --> 00:39:46.868
as being the tightly
interconnected group of neurons

00:39:46.868 --> 00:39:48.688
typically in the cortex,

00:39:48.688 --> 00:39:51.988
a single neuron connecting
to 10,000 neighbors,

